Most websites lose rankings through preventable mistakes.

## Missing or Poor Title Tags

Write unique titles under 60 characters. Format: Primary Keyword | Secondary Benefit | Brand.

## No XML Sitemap

Generate an XML sitemap through your CMS or Screaming Frog. Submit to GSC and update monthly.

## Ignoring Internal Links

Link related content together. Link outer content to service pages. Use descriptive anchor text.

## No Backlinks Strategy

Create genuinely useful content others want to reference. Focus on quality over quantity.

## Poor Metadata Implementation

Unique meta descriptions 140-160 characters per page.

## Wrong Domain Extension for Market

Use .co.uk for UK-only businesses. Use .com for international.

## Missing Schema Markup

Implement Organization, LocalBusiness, FAQ, and Article schema. Validate with Rich Results Test.

## No Hreflang for International Content

Implement hreflang tags for multiple language versions.

## Not Indexing or Indexing Wrong Pages

Check GSC coverage report. Remove noindex from important pages. Add noindex to thin pages.

## What Should You Fix First?

1. Week 1: Missing sitemaps, robots.txt, noindex problems
2. Week 2-3: Title tags, meta descriptions, schema
3. Month 1-2: Internal linking, content gaps, backlink strategy
